AttributeSet.Attribute: The term 'not provided' is registered in MedGen to support identification of submissions to ClinVar for which no condition was named when assessing the variant. 'not provided' differs from 'not specified', which is used when a variant is asserted to be benign, likely benign, or of uncertain significance for conditions that have not been specified.

Classification.Comment: This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Glu782Glyfs*4) in the MADD gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in MADD are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 32761064). This variant is present in population databases (rs754892238, gnomAD 0.0009%). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with MADD-related conditions. For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.
